The Atiku campaign organization says President Muhammadu Buhari and his deputy, Yemi Osinbajo are singing discordant tunes over calls for the restructuring of Nigeria.
Atiku campaign organization said this at the weekend while reacting to a statement credited to Professor Yemi Osinbajo that the presidential candidate of the Peoples’ Democratic Party (PDP), Atiku Abubakar, opposed the restructuring of the country when he was vice-president.
In a statement released by the group on Sunday, it accused Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo (SAN) of trying to revise history over the role Atiku Abubakar played in the actualising of restructuring.
“Professor Osinbajo needs to be reminded that there are well documented accounts in the Nigerian media chronicling Atiku Abubakar%8
